This is a re-do of the only level I made for Counter Strike - cs_velvet_elvis. This is the only level I've made for Source and plan on never doing it again. It takes way to much time.

First of all I would like to thank the creators of the Hammer editor - that's a really well made bit of software - well done. Secondly I would like to publicly curse the creators of Softimage XSI and ask the people who decided to make that the HL2 model editor WHY??? In the same tone one would ask George Lucas what he was thinking when he "sexed up" Star Wars. I also can't say I was very impressed with the amount of difficulty involved in creating and including custom textures.

To create this level I used Hammer, XSI free edition and GIMP - the coolest picture editor out there. For sound editing I used CoolEdit Pro 2 and Magix Movie Edit Pro 2004 (very easy to combine and synchronize a whole world of sounds into one wav). To package the whole thing in one bmp I used PakRat - which was easily the best tool of its kind

There are 16 start positions per side, for a total of 32 - but I've never tried running that many people. It works great with 5 per side running on a 1.92GHz AMD machine with 1GB of RAM with 9 of the 10 being Bots. Bots work (which they have to as it is a hostage map), and I suggest anyone making a hostage level create their own nav map from scratch. I tried the auto-generate, but had far more success with making my own - both for hostage movement and bot performance. CT bots will have trouble rescuing the basement and first floor hostages, but I've seen them rescue all three. Must have been a good day.

Note that Hostage performance was improved by making the area they start in nav_no_hostage - otherwise they would get stuck where they started.

The following web sites were essential to creating this level:
General level, texture, modeling and NAV edit info
http://www.hl2world.com/wiki/index.php/Main_Page#Source_Tutorials

Model tutorial
http://www.gamedesign.net/node/1002

Nav editing tutorial
http://halflife2.filefront.com/info/CSCZ_navtutorial

PakRat
http://www.geocities.com/cofrdrbob/pakrat.html

This is the Ceili's web site
http://www.ceilis.com/about/calgary_tour.html

Here's a view of the real bar (in the level it would be from sidewalk corner out front of the starbucks)
http://www.viewcalgary.com/downtown/4way.jspId=1,-8,-5

This is where I got the pictures of the police hummer
http://members.fortunecity.com/pcarsite/calgary.html

I forget where I got the Bedford lorry picture - but it is one of a lorry used by the SAS.

And last but not least, the legal history of the (former) Velvet Elvis Bar
http://www.swlearning.com/blaw/cases/stepping_on.html

Have fun with the level and if you like it - please don't shoot me if you see me online - I suck at CS and need all the help I can get. I use the name Fat Dog or Pet Monkey when playing.

Ciao.

p.s. Feel free to use anything from the level if you can get it out of the bsp
p.p.s. There realy is a pig sculpture out there in the Calgary downtown walkway system - its big and black and white and happy as can be.

scm_deathtrap_b1
Full Description Perhaps one of the most recognizable and well designed maps for the popular PS2 Multiplayer hit, Socom and Socom 2, I give you scm_deathtrap_b1 (Yeah, it's a beta). Deathtrap is a hostage rescue map (CS), but with a slight twist. The map is based of a facility ran by a terrorist group called the Iron Brotherhood, in the middle of the Thai rain forest. 3 American citizens have been kidnapped and are being held captive in this facility for weeks. Negotiations have failed and SOCOM has given the go ahead to a special joint operations team to move in and rescue the hostages. The facility is well guarded. It's elevated, has 4machine gun bunkers, hardened concrete walls, a communications tower, and only 3 points of entry; two of which are blocked from the inside and must be breached vita high explosive or a well placed gun shot. This is to be a difficult fight, with heavy loses on both sides. The counter-terrorists hostages and escort them to the extraction zone near the helicopter at the top of the hill, failure to do so will result in a mission failure. Objectives Terrorists: Defend the Facility and prevent the rescue of the hostages, or eliminate the Counter-Terrorists. Counter-Terrorists: Breach the facility and rescue/escort the hostages to the helicopter near spawn.
Features
  • Exact detail & scale from the original map
  • Custom models and textures
  • Fully Optimized
  • volumetric Fog
  • Unprecedented SOCOM-like gameplay
  • Fully functioning cubemaps, soundscapes, and ambience
  • Custom Navigation Mesh
Statistics
Solids: 547 Faces: 3366 Point Entities: 364 Solid Entities: 50 Unique Textures: 31 Texture Memory: 16.57MB Displacements: 66 Direct Lights: 28 Cubemaps: 95 Work Time: 26 Hours Final Compile Time: 6 Minutes Nav Generation Time: 23 Minutes cubemap Compilation Time: 19 Seconds

The year is 2061, the setting is at the state of the art office. Look around you; as you can see there are no computers, everyone is more mobilized with their padtops, wristtops, and braintops, so all this office needs is somewhere to sit. Of course, most of the complex is underground, but as per the new rule imposed in 2031, the elevators are shut down at the end of the day, leaving only a small part available for those who prefer to work late.

A cult has taken over-timers hostage for use of their ceremonial sacrifices, for a prophecy that has told them that they'd achieve super powers if they would; this prophecy also foretold that a group of dedicated warriors would have to battle a group of 'men in blue' during the rite that occurs before the moon is at the right place. After the rite is complete, these warriors will be the first to get the gift.

Crazed fanatics? Probably, but at least they've settled in the nicest place they could find, with the prettiest carpet, and most gorgeous lights.


Everything on the interior has special new textures, some even glow, others not so much, but at least it looks smooth, and it doesn't have any snow.

Intro:
=======
Terrorists have been been keeping Hostages against their will, along with stolen money and goods within a warehouse.
They have also constructed a network of tunnels and a bunker under the grounds.

Terrorists: Your base of operations has been compromised, a local Counter-Terror unit has been dispatched
to neutralize your team and rescue the Hostages! Stop them at all costs!

Counter-Terrorists: Intel has found the locations of a warehouse containing thousands in stolen money and goods, 
along with four captives. Your Mission: Eliminate the Terrorist threat and rescue the Hostages.

Tips:
======
Terrorists: Your spread out at first, so try to regroup, also, if you are overrun, you can retreat to the bunker. 
In the bunker, you can lock down the doors using one of the buttons in the control room, but don't let down your guard...

Counter-Terrorists: The Terrorists are spread out, so try to take them out in the pockets, but be careful that 
they don't surprise you. Also, there are also many routes to take, so be sure to learn them, such as, 
there are more ways into the bunker than just the doors...

Footnote:
=========
There are some glitches, but its my first really good map, but try to have fun!

It is a hostage rescue mission! You must rescue the hostages quickly as a counter-terrorist, and as a terrorist, you must defend the hostages, keep them in your spawn at all times!

NOTE: The nav mesh included with the map has some faults, so I recommend you generate your own in game.

You can do this by:
Opening the console up in the map, and typing in 'sv_cheats 1', then hit enter. After that, type 'nav_generate' then a new nav mesh will be generated and the server will restart with the new mesh.
